{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f1926e68-9c17-427e-ab6b-2cef63443381","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then verify:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version        # confirm 11.0.100+\ndotnet build            # ensure it compiles\ndotnet test             # run your tests\n```\n\nAlso check your NuGet packages — any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` references should be updated to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0b5a9383-fa86-4446-a5a1-a41e3be62d79","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the files clearly.","outputTokens":296,"requestId":"2836:237CD0:3660D2:400EEA:69EAC9FB"},"id":"115d3739-d3ef-46d4-8279-2153a0ec600d","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:40:18.550Z","parentId":"f705c68e-4f85-4d1a-828b-f187a8919bdd"}
